---
// Small expectation-setting block that goes ABOVE the QuoteForm.
// Keeps people honest about what we actually do with a submission and what
// happens next — no claims that we route to a specific provider, no promises
// of timing.
---
<aside
  class="bg-muted/40 border border-border rounded-xl p-5 md:p-6 mb-6"
  aria-labelledby="what-happens-next-heading"
>
  <h3
    id="what-happens-next-heading"
    class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-foreground mb-3"
  >
    What happens after you submit?
  </h3>
  <ol class="space-y-3 text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
    <li class="flex gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary text-xs font-semibold">1</span>
      <span>Your request goes to our team for review. Nothing is shared until we&rsquo;ve seen your details.</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary text-xs font-semibold">2</span>
      <span>If your job is a fit, we may forward it to an independent local junk removal provider serving the Denver metro area.</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary text-xs font-semibold">3</span>
      <span>The provider may reach out about pricing, availability, and scheduling. You&rsquo;re under no obligation to proceed after getting a quote.</span>
    </li>
  </ol>
</aside>
